description: Stock ticker symbol (unique equity identifier)
Company name / display name
End date (as-of) for which all statistics/parameters are computed
Start date of the estimation window used for returns/parameter estimation
Number of return observations used in the estimation window (after cleaning)
Spot price at asof_date (S0) from the price feed
Mean of per-period log returns over the estimation window
Std. dev. of per-period log returns over the estimation window
Annualized realized volatility from log returns (typically scaled by sqrt(annualization_factor))
Annualized downside volatility using only negative returns
Rolling 20-day annualized volatility (most recent 20 trading days)
Skewness of log-return distribution
Kurtosis of log-return distribution (dimensionless; confirm raw vs excess in your implementation)
Maximum peak-to-trough drawdown over the window (stored as a fraction)
Annualized compounded (geometric) return implied by the window’s average log return
Average daily trading volume over the most recent 20 trading days
Sample size used for the normality test (may differ from n_obs)
p-value from the chosen normality test on the target series (e.g., Shapiro-Wilk / Jarque-Bera / Anderson-Darling)
log10(normality_pvalue), used to avoid underflow showing p=0
Fraction of observations flagged as outliers under your outlier rule
Estimated GBM drift μ (annualized, real-world measure)
Estimated GBM volatility σ (annualized)
Standard error of GBM μ estimate
Standard error of GBM σ estimate
Lower bound of 95% confidence interval for GBM μ
Upper bound of 95% confidence interval for GBM μ
Lower bound of 95% confidence interval for GBM σ
Upper bound of 95% confidence interval for GBM σ
Annual dividend yield q as a decimal fraction (e.g., 0.004 = 0.4%)
Cost of carry (r - q), annualized, used for risk-neutral drift in many models
Up factor per step in the binomial/lattice model
Down factor per step in the binomial/lattice model
Real-world (historical) probability of an up move per step
Risk-neutral probability of an up move per step
Volatility implied by lattice parameters (u, d, Δt), annualized
Single Index Model (SIM) alpha, annualized (intercept)
SIM beta relative to the chosen market index
Standard error of SIM alpha estimate
Standard error of SIM beta estimate
Lower bound of 95% CI for SIM alpha
Upper bound of 95% CI for SIM alpha
Lower bound of 95% CI for SIM beta
Upper bound of 95% CI for SIM beta
R² of the SIM regression (variance explained by the index)
Std. dev. of SIM regression residuals (idiosyncratic volatility) at the data frequency
Free-text diagnostics/warnings for this row
Semicolon-delimited tags for retrieval/filtering
Date the row was exported/generated for the RAG dataset
